Sallust, however, is* wrong here. Catiline was not indicted till 65 nc. nor tried till after the election of the consuls for the year 64 B.c. The reason why he did not stand for the consulship was the refusal of the consul Tullus, on the advice of men of distinction, to recognize Catiline as a candidate.
